headline: iPhone 17 outsells predecessor by 14% in early China, US sales, research firm says
summary: BEIJING (Reuters) -Apple's iPhone 17 series outperformed its predecessor in early sales in China and the United States, research firm Counterpoint said on Monday.  Sales of the base model iPhone 17 nearly doubled in China compared to the iPhone 16 during the same period, it added, with sales of the model rising 31% across the two markets.  Apple launched the iPhone 17 series globally, including in China, in September.
